-- Hong Kong Retail Sales Increased 19.7% by Value in May From a Year Earlier
-- Sophie Leung
-- 2010-07-02T08:32:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-02/hong-kong-retail-sales-increased-19-7-by-value-in-may-from-a-year-earlier.html

          
          
             Hong Kong retail sales rose 19.7
percent in May from a year earlier, the government said today on
its website. That compared with the median 17.3 percent estimate
in a Bloomberg News survey of seven economists.  
